Position summary: The Accountant will be responsible for daily accounting tasks such as financial reporting, general ledger entries, local tax filings, recording payments and adjustments, and working closely with other departments to support budgeting, financial analysis, and financial modelling. This role is designed to support both accounting (approximately 70%) and finance-related functions (approximately 30%) to meet the increasing demands of a growing number of entities within the company.

Key Responsibilities:
Accounting Scope (70%):
• Maintain accurate books and records in compliance with Vietnamese Accounting Standards;
• Liaise with internal/external auditors, tax authorities, and relevant government bodies on accounting and finance matters;
• Receive and review supplier invoices and supporting documents; ensure accuracy and compliance with internal policies and legal regulations;
• Monitor, support, and improve accounts receivable collections;
• Work with internal teams to ensure timely and accurate customer invoicing;
• Manage accounts payable and ensure timely payments in line with contracts and approval procedures (Limits of Authority – LOA);
• Prepare AP payment vouchers to ensure payments are made accurately and on time;
• Review bank payment documentation and ensure proper controls are in place;
• Coordinate with banking partners to maintain smooth payment operations;
• Support the Manager in working with banks for senior loan arrangements, including drawdowns and repayment management;
• Maintain up-to-date accounting and operational control policies;
• Manage outsourced accounting services/agencies to ensure compliance with Vietnamese laws and accounting regulations for both the Company and its SPVs;
• Ensure timely and accurate submission of tax reports and compliance filings;

Finance Support Scope (30%):
• Assist the Finance team in budgeting, forecasting, and preparing management reports;
• Support analysis of budget vs. actual performance, and investigate key variances;
• Coordinate financial data for internal reviews and management presentations;
• Participate in financial modelling activities related to project evaluation, investment returns, and portfolio-level planning;
• Contribute to the development of tools and processes that improve financial reporting and decision-making;

Job Requirements:
• Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Accounting;
• Minimum 3 years of relevant experience (experience at multinational companies is a plus);
• Strong command of Microsoft Excel; experience with financial systems is an advantage;
• Ability to prioritize tasks, manage time effectively, and work independently;
• Proficiency in English;
• Candidates with knowledge of the renewable energy sector and experience in financial modelling for energy projects will be strongly preferred.

